cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.SE

The paper discusses security and privacy concerns in private blockchains and proposes a solution to address these concerns. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the technical aspects of implementing the proposed solution, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of blockchain technology, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
